# Design System

## Tokens, not hex

Never hardcode color values in component code. Use design tokens from `globals.css`:

| Instead of | Use |
|------------|-----|
| `#0066ff` in a component | `text-accent-blue`, `bg-accent-blue`, `border-accent-blue` |
| `#00ff88` | `text-accent-green`, `bg-accent-green` |
| `rgba(255,255,255,0.03)` | `bg-bg-tertiary`, `bg-bg-glass` |

Exception: NIST pillar colors from `NIST_COLORS` in `lib/data/dashboard.ts` may be applied via
inline `style` when dynamically mapping a NIST function to its color. This is the only acceptable
use of inline color styles.

## Glass panel

`glass-panel` is the primary surface treatment. It provides:
- Gradient background with subtle blue tint
- Border with brighter top edge
- Backdrop blur and saturation
- Inset glow shadows
- Hover state with enhanced glow

Use `<GlassPanel>` component or the `glass-panel` CSS class. Do not recreate these styles inline.

## Typography scale

All text must use Tailwind classes. No inline `style={{ fontSize: ... }}`.

| Role | Class | Size |
|------|-------|------|
| Hero title | `text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl` | 48-72px |
| Page title | `text-4xl md:text-5xl` | 36-48px |
| Section heading | `text-2xl md:text-3xl` | 24-30px |
| Card header | `text-sm font-medium` | 14px |
| Body text | `text-sm font-light` | 14px |
| KPI number | `text-2xl glow-number` | 24px |
| Label / metadata | `text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wide` | 11px |
| Contextual heading | `text-2xl font-extralight` | 24px |
| Document subsection | `text-sm font-medium` | 14px |
| **Minimum** | `text-[11px]` | **11px â€” nothing below** |

Exceptions: error boundaries (`error.tsx`, `global-error.tsx`) and legal page subsection headings
(`LegalPageTemplate`) use smaller heading scales appropriate to their context. These are not page
section headings and should not be flagged.

## Font weight

- Headlines: `font-extralight` (200)
- Body: `font-light` (300)
- Labels: `font-medium` (500)
- Never use `font-bold` or `font-semibold` â€” the aesthetic is restrained, not loud.

## Spacing

- Section padding: `px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-32`
- Inter-section gap: `space-y-8` when inside a continuous flow
- Card internal padding: `p-4` to `p-5`
- Gap between cards: `gap-3`

## Animation

Available keyframes: `fadeIn`, `glow-pulse`, `status-breathe`, `holo-sweep`.
Use `animate-[name_duration_easing]` syntax. Prefer subtle, slow animations (3-8 second cycles).
No bouncing, no attention-grabbing motion.

## The intelligence aesthetic

The site should feel like a classified briefing document:
- Dark backgrounds (`#0a0a0f`)
- Restrained color â€” accent blue is the primary highlight, used sparingly
- Monospace for data values (`font-mono tabular-nums`)
- Uppercase tracking for labels and metadata
- Technical vocabulary, not marketing fluff
- Dashed lines, not solid borders, for connectors
- Glow effects suggest active systems, not decoration
